.PP
.if n *
.if t \(bu
There are some additional reports available via the web interface.
They are mainly to extract error causes and trends from the project
history statistics.
.PP
.if n *
.if t \(bu
There have been a number of minor bug fixes concerning the handling of
old 2.3 projects.  This should ease transition for users with existing
2.3 projects.
.PP
.if n *
.if t \(bu
A bug in aecp -delta has been fixed, where Aegis was trying to find
change state files one branch level too high.
.PP
.if n *
.if t \(bu
There is now a re-try performed when a stale NFS file handle error is
detected.  This should make it easier for some sites which are heavily
networked.
.PP
.if n *
.if t \(bu
There have been some improvements to the way Control-C is handled.
It should be more responsive when waiting for locks.
.PP
.if n *
.if t \(bu
Project administrators may now end development of a branch.  Since
branches can endure for months or years, the orginal branch creator may
have moved on.  This copes with this situation.
